Class Project_managementValueInputController

  • public class Project_managementValueInputController
extends ValueInputController
    Controller class for a value input component.

    A value input component contains an arbitrary number of stacked input value fields. Each input valued field is assigned to an input value. For each input value of the application there exists a DataServicePool class, which holds service instances and other related information for the input value.

    A stacked input value field allows the user to set the value which is managed by the ValueDataManager of the data service pool of the assigned input value. Each stacked input value field of an value input component is initialized by setting up the validation (ValidationService) of the input field, setting up an autocomplete popup (AutocompletePopupController) for the input field, binding the value of the value data manager to the input field and registering the execution status and the data status of the input field to the status managers of the application (DataStatusManager, ExecutionStatusManager).
